{"id":114,"date":"2016-01-17T18:29:20","date_gmt":"2016-01-18T02:29:20","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/murphlaw.net\/?page_id=114"},"modified":"2023-10-02T10:58:43","modified_gmt":"2023-10-02T17:58:43","slug":"employment-law-attorneys-los-angeles-ventura-county","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/areas-of-expertise\/employment-law-attorneys-los-angeles-ventura-county\/","title":{"rendered":"Employment Law Attorneys"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"pl-114\" class=\"panel-layout\">\n<div id=\"pg-114-0\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\n<div id=\"pgc-114-0-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"1\">\n<h2 id=\"panel-114-0-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-headline panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"0\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 36px;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-671 alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Employment-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"375\" height=\"294\" srcset=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Employment-2.jpg 970w, https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Employment-2-300x236.jpg 300w, https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Employment-2-768x603.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 375px) 100vw, 375px\" \/><\/span> Fresno &amp; Fresno Employment Law Attorneys Committed to Working for You<\/h2>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pg-114-1\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\n<div id=\"pgc-114-1-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<div id=\"panel-114-1-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"1\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n<p>Workspace and professional relationships should be built on respect, integrity, equality, and safety. Sadly, that\u2019s not always the case. Instances of discrimination, harassment, and otherwise hazardous working conditions do arise, and these situations can put you or your loved ones in financial, physical, or mental danger.<\/p>\n<p>With over a combined 40 years of legal experience, we\u2019ve been able to work on behalf of both employers and employees to find justice.\u00a0 If you\u2019ve recently been a victim of workplace discrimination in the  Fresno or Fresno county areas, or feel that your workplace rights have been neglected or denied, the <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/about-us\/\">Chuckstern Murphy Law Firm<\/a> can help.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pg-114-2\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\n<div id=\"pgc-114-2-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"1\">\n<div id=\"panel-114-2-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"3\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<p class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">And, with two law office locations, you can navigate the complexities of your case with an attorney in areas such as  Fresno, Burbank, Camarillo, Newbury Park, Thousand Oaks, and Fresno.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<h2>Honoring Employer &amp; Employee Rights<\/h2>\n<div id=\"panel-114-2-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"3\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n<p>We recognize that both employees and employers can face injustice in the workplace, and therefore it\u2019s essential that our employment law attorneys in  Fresno and Fresnno County are well versed in the finer nuances that govern employment law.<\/p>\n<p>Businesses that seek the assistance of Chuckstern Murphy Law Firm reserve their right to employ individuals who are loyal, honest, and act with the company\u2019s best interest in mind. That includes ensuring that employees uphold performance expectations, maintain proprietary or otherwise protected company information, and comply with legally binding agreements.<\/p>\n<h2>Employment Law Experience<\/h2>\n<p>There are numerous reasons why an individual or organization may need the immediate counsel of an employment law expert, and it\u2019s our goal to work closely with clients to identify their needs and offer them compassionate service while providing aggressive representation in the courtroom.<\/p>\n<p>With <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/case-results\/\">years of experience<\/a>, we are prepared to handle cases in the following areas of employment law.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wrongful Termination in Violation of Public Policy<\/li>\n<li>Discrimination (age, race, religion, gender, medical condition, physical or mental disability, sexual orientation, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>Retaliation<\/li>\n<li>Statutory Protected Leave of Absence\n<ul>\n<li>Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA)<\/li>\n<li>California Family Rights Act (CFRA)<\/li>\n<li>Fair Employment &amp; Housing Act (FEHA)<\/li>\n<li>Americans with Disability Act (ADA)<\/li>\n<li>Pregnancy Disability Leave (PDL)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Failure to Provide Reasonable Accommodations<\/li>\n<li>Failure to Participate in a Meaningful Interactive Process<\/li>\n<li>Sexual Harassment<\/li>\n<li>Hostile Work Environment<\/li>\n<li>Wage &amp; Hour Law Disputes<\/li>\n<li>Employment Agreements<\/li>\n<li>Independent Contractor Agreements<\/li>\n<li>Employee Misclassification Disputes<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>History of Success<\/h2>\n<p>Our clients have access to heavy-hitting trial attorneys who have extensive experience, diversified knowledge, and integrity that\u2019s required to guide our clients through the most complex legal battles.<\/p>\n<p>There is no case too small, and every client &#8211;\u00a0 individuals or large, multi-national corporations &#8211; will receive the highest quality of service and most personal level of attention.<\/p>\n<p>Our highly skilled litigators and legal professionals, including our employment law attorneys in  Fresno and Fresnno County, have successfully settled hundreds of lawsuits and handled over 90 trials.<\/p>\n<p>In addition, we have been retained to serve as Cumis counsel on a multitude of cases, and have repeatedly led clients on the path to <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/case-results\/\">justice and success<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>You deserve to maintain your rights as an employee or an employer, and we look forward to making sure that you receive the justice you deserve.<\/p>\n<h2>Contingency Fee Agreements<\/h2>\n<p>We know that victims of employment law violations often struggle with subsequent financial fallout, and that\u2019s why we will enter into contingency fee agreements in certain cases.<\/p>\n<p>Under a contingency fee agreement, we will cover all or a significant portion of litigation-related fees, including but not limited to court filings fees, deposition fees, travel expenses, attorney service fees, investigation fees, and subpoenas fees.<\/p>\n<p>In exchange, clients must agree to pay our law office a percentage of settlement proceeds or jury verdict at the close of the case or trial.<\/p>\n<p>Find out how we can help you by calling our  Fresno office at 415-217-9456 or our Fresno office at 415-217-9456. Or, sign up for a\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/contact-us\/fresno-office\/\">free consultation online<\/a>\u00a0or contact us online at our <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/contact-us\/fresno-office\/\"> Fresno<\/a> or <a href=\"https:\/\/murphla